p there.  FV is like Sweden -- nice country with a slight negative population growth.  AO was like Europe during the black-death. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 469<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 8:40:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think ..</span><hr size=1> That's just it though, Bjond.<br><br>I have seen <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> nothing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to indicate that our server population is dwindling.  <br><br>While I have seen a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> few</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> higher level players leave the server, I've also seen a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ton</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of newbies starting out here, especially players new to EQ in general.<br><br>If I had to guess, I'd say our server is slowly <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> growing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  You're basing our server's population on the activities of the 30+ crowd, which is hardly fair, especially when you consider that the majority of our server is still enjoying the lower levels of the game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 10:05:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I see a ton ..</span><hr size=1> .. of new newbies all the time, too.  I just don't see the same ones leveling beyond the &quot;newbie&quot; levels.  We get a fresh crop all the time.  I have 2 alts in the &quot;newbie&quot; levels, too, so I do see folks lower than my monk (who, at 24, is just beyond &quot;newbie&quot; and into the &quot;lowbie&quot; levels now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br><br>I've met some really fantastic completely-new-to-EQ newbies.  They're all gone now and I don't know why -- they just vanish.  'Dunno if it was server or EQ or other game or what.  I have guesses and suspicions, but I don't know for sure.  I wish more would stay, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 471<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 10:53:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I see a ton ..</span><hr size=1>    Judging from my experience as an EQ newbie, it's probably a lot of this...<br><br>[Me] I'm gettin my butt kicked<br>[Some other guy] What's your Int<br>[Me] 114<br>[Other guy] As a dark elf necro?  Where'd you put all your starting stats?<br>[Me] I put most of it in strength and agility, I wanted to be kind of a tank-necro.<br>[Otherguy] lol!  All you need is Int, and lots of it!<br>[Me] Bah, time to remake <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 1:42:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I see a ton ..</span><hr size=1> Hmph.  I think alot of things cause people to quit.  Especially the newer players.<br><br>Twinkiness.  Alot of people may have read boards, have friends who played, etc, and are thoroughly disappointed because they logged on and didn't automatically get 300 plat plopped in their laps.  And yes, I have met someone who complained about this.<br><br>TLC &amp; Language Barrier.  I don't think it's so much in game, but people peruse boards like this, like the ones at eqvault, etc, and they see complaint after complaint on how they both suck, how they make the game harder, etc.  This makes them afraid of missing something, or makes them wonder what they're missing out on.<br><br>Newness.  Every time I hear a newbie /shout Help! I try my best to tell them of the /yell command, but as there are alot on this server that came here to get away from the dregs of the other servers, they may not be as patient to explain things.  Thus, the other servers seem friendlier.<br><br>Grouping.  Not so much the lack of people, as newbie zones seem well stocked, but I think some people may want to play the Drizzt Do'Urden dark elf that hangs out with dwarves and humans, and here they don't even have that option.  Alot of people that fancy themselves roleplaying fans don't get much more than a video game and some fantasy books, as evidenced by the huge amounts of names ripped off of literature, video games, etc.<br><br>Newness 2.  I know that when I first started playing, I wasn't sure at all what I wanted to play.  So one the servers I played on, I had a large variety of characters that never even got past third level before I decided that class wouldn't pan out for me.  Here, we don't have extra characters per account, so the people have to delete their character to try something new.  They may go to other servers, or they may just be deleting and starting over time and time again (making them seem to disappear).<br><br>Other stuff.  Basically, put here anything I forgot.  And include stuff that keeps out powergamers, pharmers, etc, because there are some that find the challenge of TLC to not be worth it. <p><center><font size=+2><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bmaidensfancy">Shiden Kaidan</a></font><br>Tier'dal Knight<br><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/"> Firiona Vie</a><br><font size=1><font color=red>@}</font><font color=green>--,--'---- </font></font><br><i>"You have no power over me."</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 2:34:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I think ..</span><hr size=1> .. I probably classify as a light PG'er.  I do have two accounts and two comps.  I revived an old defunct PC for the express purpose of having two PCs in EQ at the same time -- not so they could group (gah!), but for item transfers and ports and languages.  I can honestly say that if I did not have two accounts/comps I absolutely would not have come to FV.<br><br>EQ with 2x2 is the only reasonable way around the language issue.  Having at least one alternate character is the only reasonable way around many in-game issues, including TLC.  And, lately I've found I spend about 90% of my time just plain running about.  Boy do I miss my taxi, err, wizard.  Bless the wonderful Neriak slave market for selling hobbit druids so cheaply.  I got a great deal -- they were just going to sell her to the ogres as an hors'd'ovre.  I only wish they sold them higher than level 1.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Basically, a more difficult ruleset makes power-gaming more attractive and creates a wider seperation between those that do and those that don't.  If you know EQ and play on FV, you're likely thinking either &quot;thank god I have 2 acc/comps&quot; or &quot;damn I wish I did&quot;.  There will always be an advantage to having more RL-cash, but it would be nice if the game didn't promote it so heavily.  I think the ruleset could have been far more supportive of RP without the difficulty burden.<br><br>Anyway, I put my 2nd comp behind me on the other side of my office just so I wouldn't use it for PL'ing.  I want to play one character at a time for many reasons and I need to keep temptation at least at arms reach.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroawen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roawen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 5:51:38 am)</font><br>