r>As for population... we've seen quite an influx in these past weeks of people joining us --- either new players, or players coming from other servers.  Yes, we've lost a few players to go back to their original servers, but we've gained (lately) more than we've lost... and I think over the coming weeks that is a trend that will continue.<br><br>Castinare Eleas<br>Ranger, on the 26th Branch of the Tree of Tunare<br>Officer, Court of the Crosswinds <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 9:54:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bjond</span><hr size=1> Bjond, Bjond, Bjond<br><br>     You just keep coming at it from the power gaming/high level view point.<br><br>&lt;Quote&gt; &quot;I can honestly say that if I did not have two accounts/comps I absolutely would not have come to FV.<br>Basically, a more difficult ruleset makes power-gaming more attractive and creates a wider seperation between those that do and those that don't. If you know EQ and play on FV, you're likely thinking either &quot;thank god I have 2 acc/comps&quot; or &quot;damn I wish I did&quot;<br><br>This is exactly my point. This server was not designed for power leveling, farming etc.. It was designed for roleplaying. As such I see it doing very well indeed! What you are complaining about is the high level game and if it REALLY made power gaming so attractive, why are alot of higher level characters leaving? And if you think 24 is a lowbie, maybe you need to be on a different server.<br><br>Lexxi Ledenyetz<br>25th Prayer<br>Cleric of Brell<br>Ak'Anon<br>Moral Officer - Ledenyetz Troupe<br><br>PS. My guild and my friends list grows everyday, is that a negative population growth? &lt;Sticks tongue out&gt;<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A> at: 1/22/02 11:45:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarlithas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karlithas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 10:54:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bjond</span><hr size=1> I have one computer and one account, and I say to myself everyday &quot;DAMN! i am Glad that I play on FV!&quot;  Guess it's just different prespective.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Besides, I am really appreciative of current server population.  Coming from BS server, I find it refreshing not to have to get in a waiting list to fight orcs.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarlithas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karlithas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/22/02 10:57:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uranion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 12:13:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.landofthelost.com/enicklogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Server health=Excellent</span><hr size=1> I just started on the FV server this weekend and I have loved every second of it so far. Having played EQ for a couple years, the rule set of this server is a refreshing change. I didn't think I could ever recreate the feeling I had when I played EQ for the first time, but playing on this server I see I was wrong. Who would have thought I could get so excited again over owning leather armor? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>There are a couple of main advantages I see in this server when compared to the other non-PvP servers. Most of this may seem obvious, but I'll mention it anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>The first advantage I see is the lack of twinking. Not that there is anything wrong with twinking, but the immersive nature of EQ is sort of shot when people sit around trying to get items for other characters. I mean, this isn't K-MART, right? Every player I see on FV I know is playing because they like that character, not because they want to accrue high level items for their lower level characters. Somehow, this  makes the environment a lot more realistic. <br><br>The second advantage is the language barrier. I mean, honestly, I can't understand why different languages were ever put into into EQ when the common language existed. Having your own race specific language really gives your character a unique feel. And the process of learning other languages is a lot of fun. I had never focused on developing language skills until I came to this server, and probably never would have if it hadn't been for the FV rule set. <br><br>The last major advantage I can see is somewhat tough to put a finger on, but basically the environment just FEELS less rushed. On other servers I have played on, people are always cramming for experience and/or trying to get something done as soon as possible. Here, I feel more relaxed, like I can take my time. The people I have grouped with thus far really enjoy the environment the game creates, as opposed to enjoying gaining levels. <br><br>Anyhow, just thought I would mention this for what its worth. I hope this server stays just as it is for a long long time to come. <br><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uranion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranion</A> at: 1/22/02 12:15:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukan1301.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kan1301</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 12:17:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bjond</span><hr size=1> You must be blind to say server population is excellent.<br>Wait till you can't solo anymore which is around level 30, then tell me we don't need more people on this server. I am not playing necro druid which can solo to 60. Even my cleric has to spend hours to get a group. RP or not you need exp. No group=no exp.  I'm also in a big guild.  We have 30 people on sometimes, it's still very hard to get a group.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://